<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="559" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/3207</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                President <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-05">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 5, 1917</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: The enclosed telegram
                            has just been received from Minister Gonzales, at Habana.<note n="91" xml:id="d559fn1">
                                <ref target="frus1917Supp01v01#pg_221">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 221</ref>.</note> I would like
                            to know your wishes in the reply I am to make to this dispatch. I think
                            we should consider very seriously requesting the Cuban Government to
                            remove the German Consuls and breaking off relations, in view of the
                            proximity of Cuba to this country and to our West Indian
                            possessions.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>